# VidTube Dockerization Implementation Plan

This plan details how to package the VidTube backend, frontend (using Nginx), and Redis services into Docker containers, allowing you to run the entire project with a single command on any machine.

---

## User Review Required

Please review the proposed container layout:

> [!NOTE]
> **Container Networking**
> In Docker, containers talk to each other using their service names as hostnames.
> - The backend will connect to Redis via `redis://redis:6379` (instead of `127.0.0.1:6379`).
> - The frontend Nginx proxy will forward API calls to `http://backend:3000`.

> [!TIP]
> **Database Host**
> We will continue to use your MongoDB Atlas connection string (cloud database) so you don't lose your existing database records.

